additional notes

Attic

The attic had wooden siding installed over the rafters, and the rafter bays were insulated. Holes were drilled into the roof sheathing to obtain moisture readings. No elevated moisture levels were identified at the time of assessment. The drilled locations were subsequently sealed with brown caulking.

Fungal growth was observed on the wooden siding covering the rafter bays on the attic side, exposed to the open attic air. The growth was sporadic throughout the attic; however, in areas where it was present, it appeared heavy.

The attic access exhibited evidence of air infiltration and may require improved sealing, such as the installation of a gasket.

HVAC System

The HVAC system exhibited evidence of fungal growth within the unit. The observed growth did not appear heavy and was limited to sporadic reservoirs.

A tape lift sample was collected from within the HVAC system, which confirmed the presence of fungal growth.

Interior – First Story

The flooring on the first story had separated. No visible fungal growth was observed directly on the floor at the time of assessment; however, due to the condition and prior history, sampling was performed.

A tape lift sample was collected at the baseboard along the corner of the wall adjacent to the area where the floor had separated to evaluate the potential influence of crawl space air. Fungal growth had previously been identified on furniture in this location, indicating a possible source of contamination.

Additional Sampling

A tape lift sample was collected from the wooden siding at the roof sheathing within the attic. Laboratory analysis indicated heavy fungal growth at this location.
